
======================================================================
EXAMPLE 1: 5-TEAM SPORTS ROUND-ROBIN
======================================================================
Teams: Arrows, Bears, Cubs, Ducks, Eagles


============================================================
5-Team Round-Robin (Transitive with A-B-C cycle)
============================================================
Options (5): ['Arrows', 'Bears', 'Cubs', 'Ducks', 'Eagles']

Win counts (Copeland scores):
  Arrows              : 3/4 wins
  Bears               : 3/4 wins
  Cubs                : 3/4 wins
  Ducks               : 1/4 wins
  Eagles              : 0/4 wins

No Condorcet winner (cyclic preferences exist)

OCF Analysis:
  3-cycles: 1, 5-cycles: 0
  Total odd cycles: 1
  H(T) exact: 3
  OCF: H = 1×1 + 1×2 = 3
  OCF verified: 3 = 3 [OK]

Interpretation:
  H(T) = 3 consistent linear orderings
  More orderings = MORE ambiguity / LESS decisiveness
  Minimum possible H = 1 (totally transitive = perfect ranking)
  H for this n = 1: perfect transitivity

  3-cycle count = 1 (Condorcet paradoxes)
  Disjoint cycle pairs = 0 (compound paradoxes)
  Cycles exist but all share vertices: SIMPLE preference cycles

  H/H_max = 3/15 = 0.200

